						<summary>

						<p>Slab fixed into a wall of the Kalamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Śivachitta Vīra-Permāḍi 12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This mutilated inscription refers itself to the reign of Śivachitta-Vīra-Permāḍi It is dated • • • vyaya, Āshāḍha, śu. (5) Sunday.</p>						

						<p>It registers the gift of land to the god Grāmēśvara by the king who is stated to have been ruling Palasige Twelve-Thousand and Koṁkaṇa-Nine-Hundred. Mentions the deities Bāṇakēśvara and Byāseśvara.</p>						

						</summary>
